I am a PhD student in Computer Science at Yale University, advised by [Arman Cohan](http://armancohan.com/). My research interests are in the intersection of AI and cognitive science, and my research aims to understand, extend, and improve the capabilities of large language models (LLMs) by drawing inspiration from human metacognition. I am grateful to be supported by the [NSF Graduate Research Fellowship](nsfgrfp.org).
<!-- I aim to draw inspiration from theories of human cognition and cognitive bias to model judgment, behavior, and ethics in AI agents. -->

As an undergraduate at MIT, I explored research topics in meta-reinforcement learning at the [Computational Cognitive Science Lab](https://cocosci.mit.edu/) under [Josh Tenenbaum](http://web.mit.edu/cocosci/josh.html) and Bayesian nonparametrics at the [Fiete Lab](https://fietelab.mit.edu/) under [Ila Fiete](https://mcgovern.mit.edu/profile/ila-fiete/). I also studied the metacognition of emotion in the [Explorer of Perception and Attention Lab](http://epa.psy.ntu.edu.tw/) with [Su-Ling Yeh](http://epa.psy.ntu.edu.tw/SuLingYeh_eng.html) at National Taiwan University and trustworthy AI methods in the [Collaborative, Learning, and Adaptive Robots Lab](https://clear-nus.github.io/) with [Harold Soh](https://haroldsoh.com/) at National University of Singapore with generous support from the [Fung Foundation](https://www.fungfoundation.org/).
